2023) was an American film editor. Filmography as editor includes The Black Stallion, Raising Cain, Jumanji, Jurassic Park III and Hidalgo, October Sky, and The Prize Winner of Defiance, Ohio. He also directed the film The Black Stallion Returns (1983).\nDalva was nominated for the Academy Award for Best Film Editing for his work on The Black Stallion (1979).\nDalva was an alumnus of Colgate University and member of Phi Kappa Tau fraternity.\nDalva was elected to membership in the American Cinema Editors, and was considered to be part of a core group of successful filmmakers known as The Dirty Dozen, who were film students at the University of Southern California in the 1960s.\nDalva died from lymphoma in Larkspur, California, on January 27, 2023, at the age of 80.\n\n", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2023-08-01T16:48:29.935848+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 2969, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_Dalva"}], "uuid": "c162d3db-d1ff-4e43-9bec-403da0bcbecb", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "27691", "external_references": [{"id": 12609, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q2156838"}, {"id": 12610, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "4655283"}, {"id": 12611, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "no2005008849"}, {"id": 12612, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-no2005008849"}], "date_modified": "2023-09-06T00:40:26.322608+10:00"}, {"id": 76743, "name": "Ian Bone", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2649119, "title": "Play School. Hats", "work_id": 80879, "role": "producer/director", "role_id": 31, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "", "date_of_death": "", "genders": [], "languages": [], "places_of_operation": [], "biography": "", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2023-05-09T15:39:42.088170+10:00", "external_links": [], "uuid":